### Use case

```dart
  /// The offset of the menu relative to the alignment origin determined by
  /// [MenuStyle.alignment] on the [style] attribute and the ambient
  /// [Directionality].
```
Currently `MenuAnchor`  uses the ambient `Directionality` to decide if the menu should align to the left or to the right. For example you need rtl direction for effect like this
<img width="151" height="205" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e4802c6f-3d5e-4cc1-8bb1-d9399776d9fb" />

There is no way to specify a direction for the `MenuAnchor`.  You can provide `Directionality` in the tree, but it is unintuitive and you also need to switch back the directionality for each children.

```dart
class MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyWidget({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Center(
      child: Directionality(
        textDirection: TextDirection.rtl,
        child: MenuAnchor(
          style: MenuStyle(alignment: Alignment.bottomRight),
          menuChildren: [
            Directionality(
              textDirection: TextDirection.ltr,
              child: ListTile(
                title: Text("Item 1"),
              ),
            ),
            Directionality(
              textDirection: TextDirection.ltr,
              child: ListTile(
                title: Text("Item 2"),
              ),
            ),
          ],
          builder: (context, controller, child) {
            return IconButton(
              onPressed: controller.open,
              icon: Icon(Icons.add),
            );
          },
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}


```

### Proposal

Add an direction option for `MenuAnchor`
```dart
class MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyWidget({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MenuAnchor(
      style: MenuStyle(alignment: AlignmentGeometry.bottomRight),
      direction: TextDirection.rtl,
      menuChildren: [
        ListTile(
          title: Text("Item 1"),
        ),
        ListTile(
          title: Text("Item 2"),
        ),
      ],
    );
  }
}
```
I can work on a PR if the team think it is OK to add this new option.

